{"lemma":"أَفْصَح","slug":"أَفْصَح","root":"ف.ص.ح","root_slug":"ف-ص-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ص-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَفْصَح","root":"فصح","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33967","n33973"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%92%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%AD"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33967","headword_ar":"افصح","root":"fSH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, first sentence, in two places. ―         -b2-  It is also said of urine, (K, TA,) as mentioned by IAar, but not expl. by him, (TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It became clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from turbidness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfSHt","text_ar":"افصحت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said of a ewe, or she-goat, (S, A, K,) and of a she-camel, (TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Her milk became free from admixture;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from froth, and clear of its biestings:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her biestings ceased, and the milk came after:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her biestings ceased, and her milk became free from admixture."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b4-  And [hence]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfSH","text_ar":"افصح"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He spoke with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSaAHap","text_ar":"فَصَاحَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clearness, perspicuousness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distinctness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to the explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fSAHp","text_ar":"فصاحة"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the K, and the usage of this verb in numerous exs.; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with chasteness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"correctness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfSH AlkalaAma","text_ar":"افصح الكَلَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfSH bihi","text_ar":"افصح بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfSH","text_ar":"افصح"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqawola","text_ar":"القَوْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but when the verb became in frequent use, and commonly known, the objective complement became dropped, as in the case of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHosana","text_ar":"اَحْسَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.: (TA:) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he spoke clearly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plainly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * K, *"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2404},{"kind":"text","text":"TA,) to another; (A, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without indistinctness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without concealment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [and] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a foreigner)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spoke Arabic:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spoke Arabic correctly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, Msb:) [and] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man of barbarous or vitious or indistinct speech)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spoke intelligibly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfSH fiY","text_ar":"افصح فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manoTiqihi","text_ar":"مَنْطِقِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a child)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"began to speak intelligibly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfSH fulaAnN vum~a faSuHa","text_ar":"افصح فُلَانٌ ثُمَّ فَصُحَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He spoke Arabic, and then became good in his language,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dialect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so accord. to Er-Rághib, as cited in the Mz, 9th"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwE","text_ar":"نوع"},{"kind":"text","text":"; in which it is said that some, but not so correctly, use these two verbs in the converse manner: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he spoke clearly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligibly, and then became chaste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good and correct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eloquent, in his speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"language"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfSH","text_ar":"افصح"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used in poetry as signifying (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(an animal not endowed with speech)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uttered a sound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cry, clearly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfSH","text_ar":"افصح"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano $aYo'K","text_ar":"عَنْ شَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ifoSaAHN","text_ar":"اـِفْصَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in this and the preceding senses], meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He explained a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfSH Eano muraAdihi","text_ar":"افصح عَنْ مُرَادِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He showed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revealed"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his desire"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his meaning"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b5-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became clearly apparent, manifest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evident."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfSH AlS~uboHu","text_ar":"افصح الصُّبْحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The daybreak became clearly apparent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the light of daybreak appeared."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfSH Alr~ajulu mino ka*aA","text_ar":"افصح الرَّجُلُ مِنْ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man got clear out of such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"escaped from it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nufoSiHu mino $itaAy^inaA","text_ar":"نُفْصِحُ مِنْ شِتَايِنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We shall get clear out of our winter."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoSaHuwA","text_ar":"اَفْصَحُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the Christians, S, A, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"entered upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"celebrated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the festival called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfiSoH","text_ar":"الفِصْح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Easter"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and broke their fast, eating flesh-meat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [And said also of Jews, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They celebrated the Passover:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfiSoHu","text_ar":"الفِصْحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","A","Lh","Msb","ISk"]},{"entry_id":"n33973","headword_ar":"اَفْصَحُ","root":"fSH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, chaste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fra from barbarousness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: in the Kur xxviii. 34, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more clear"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perspicuous"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distinct"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in tongue] (Jel.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}